  "text": "All TypeScript module resolution source code in the microsoft/TypeScript repository under src/compiler/ is concentrated in a single primary file: src/compiler/moduleNameResolver.ts. This file implements the complete module resolution system for all resolution strategies.\n\n## Entry Point and Strategy Dispatch\n\nThe main entry point is the **resolveModuleName** function (line 1401), which handles the strategy dispatch based on the ModuleResolutionKind compiler option. The switch statement (lines 1434-1452) branches to different resolver implementations:\n- **Node16**: node16ModuleNameResolver (line 1436)\n- **NodeNext**: nodeNextModuleNameResolver (line 1439)\n- **Node10**: nodeModuleNameResolver (line 1442)\n- **Classic**: classicNameResolver (line 1445)\n- **Bundler**: bundlerModuleNameResolver (line 1448)\n\n## Node16/NodeNext Module Resolution\n\nThe **node16ModuleNameResolver** (line 1704) and **nodeNextModuleNameResolver** (line 1717) both delegate to **nodeNextModuleNameResolverWorker** (line 1730), which handles the modern Node.js resolution features including:\n- ESM mode detection via resolution mode\n- Extension handling (TypeScript, JavaScript, Declaration, JSON)\n- Features flags (NodeResolutionFeatures) for conditional exports and imports\n\nThese delegate to **nodeModuleNameResolverWorker** (line 1795), which coordinates the full resolution pipeline including baseUrl/paths resolution, optional resolution settings, and fallback strategies.\n\n## Package.json Exports Field Resolution\n\nExports field resolution is implemented through:\n- **loadModuleFromExports** (line 2613): Handles conditional exports for the main entry point (.)\n- **loadModuleFromExportsOrImports** (line 2702): Core logic for matching specifiers against export/import patterns\n- **loadModuleFromTargetExportOrImport** (nested in line 2745): Recursive processor for target resolution with subpath support\n- **comparePatternKeys** (line 2688): Implements Node.js spec sorting for pattern priority\n- Pattern matching with trailers support via NodeResolutionFeatures.ExportsPatternTrailers\n\n## Imports Field Resolution\n\n- **loadModuleFromImports** (line 2650): Handles package.json imports field for #-prefixed specifiers\n- **loadModuleFromSelfNameReference** (line 2575): Resolves self-references using the package name\n\n## Classic Resolution\n\nThe **classicNameResolver** (line 3250) provides legacy TypeScript module resolution:\n- Attempts resolution with settings (baseUrl, paths, rootDirs)\n- Walks ancestor directories for non-relative module names\n- Uses caching for non-relative names (tryFindNonRelativeModuleNameInCache)\n\n## Path Mapping Resolution\n\nPath mapping is handled by:\n- **tryLoadModuleUsingPaths** (line 3158): Matches module names against paths patterns using matchPatternOrExact\n- **tryLoadModuleUsingOptionalResolutionSettings** (line 1550): Coordinates baseUrl/paths/rootDirs resolution\n- **tryLoadModuleUsingPathsIfEligible** (line 1562): Eligibility checks for path-based resolution\n\n## Package.json Information Caching and Loading\n\n- **getPackageJsonInfo** (line 2440): Reads and caches package.json with lazy-loaded fields (versionPaths, resolvedEntrypoints, peerDependencies)\n- **getPackageScopeForPath** (line 2394): Walks ancestor directories to find containing package.json scope\n- **isPackageJsonInfo** (line 920): Type guard to distinguish valid package.json info from failed lookups\n- **getTemporaryModuleResolutionState** (line 2355): Creates resolution state for temporary lookups\n\n## Tracing and Diagnostics\n\nResolution tracing is managed by:\n- **trace** function (line 115): Outputs diagnostic messages when traceResolution is enabled\n- **isTraceEnabled** (line 120): Checks if tracing is enabled via compiler options and host\n- **ModuleResolutionState.reportDiagnostic** (line 2355): Collects resolution diagnostics for error reporting\n\nThe tracing system logs key resolution steps including:\n- Module resolution kind selection\n- Cache hits/misses\n- Pattern matching results\n- File existence checks\n- Conditional exports matching\n- Package.json field lookups\n\n## Node Modules Directory Walking\n\n- **loadModuleFromNearestNodeModulesDirectory** (line 2984): Entry point for node_modules resolution\n- **loadModuleFromNearestNodeModulesDirectoryWorker** (line 2993): Implements the walking algorithm with two-pass logic (prioritizing TypeScript/Declaration files)\n- **loadModuleFromNearestNodeModulesDirectoryTypesScope** (line 2988): @types package resolution\n- **resolveFromTypeRoot** (line 3321): Fallback to typeRoots when declaration files aren't found\n\n## File Resolution\n\n- **loadModuleFromFile** (line 2064): Attempts to load from file with extension matching/replacement\n- **loadModuleFromFileNoPackageId** (line 2056): File loading without package ID assignment\n- **nodeLoadModuleByRelativeName** (line 1978): Relative path resolution with package.json integration\n- **loadNodeModuleFromDirectory** (line 2209): Directory resolution with package.json field processing\n\n## Package.json Field Processing\n\n- **readPackageJsonTypesFields** (line 394): Reads 'typings' or 'types' field\n- **readPackageJsonMainField** (line 403): Reads 'main' field\n- **readPackageJsonPathField**: Generic field reader with path resolution\n- **getVersionPathsOfPackageJsonInfo**: Handles typesVersions field with version matching\n\n## Key Data Structures\n\n- **PathAndExtension** (line 170): Result of file resolution before package ID assignment\n- **Resolved** (line 152): Complete resolution with path, extension, and optional package ID\n- **ModuleResolutionState** (line 315): Stateful context carrying host, compiler options, cache, tracing, and diagnostic reporting\n- **PackageJsonInfo** (line 2374): Cached package.json with lazy-loaded supplementary fields\n- **NodeResolutionFeatures**: Enum controlling enabled resolution features (Exports, Imports, ExportsPatternTrailers, EsmMode, etc.)\n\n## Helper Functions\n\n- **parsePackageName** (line 2558): Splits module name into package and subpath components\n- **parseNodeModuleFromPath** (line 2036): Extracts package directory from resolved file path\n- **allKeysStartWithDot** (line 2567): Validates exports object structure\n- **getTypesPackageName** (line 3200): Maps package names to @types equivalents\n- **mangleScopedPackageName** (line 3205): Encodes scoped package names for @types lookup\n- **traceIfEnabled**: Conditional tracing helper function\n- **getNodeResolutionFeatures** (line 723): Determines enabled Node resolution features from compiler options\n- **getConditions** (line varying): Maps resolution mode to condition strings for export field matching\n\n## Supporting Files\n\nWhile the core implementation is in moduleNameResolver.ts, the following files provide essential definitions and utilities:\n- **src/compiler/types.ts**: Type definitions (ModuleResolutionKind, ModuleResolutionHost, ModuleResolutionCache)\n- **src/compiler/utilities.ts**: Helper function matchPatternOrExact for path pattern matching\n- **src/compiler/program.ts**: Integration with program creation and module resolution caching"
}

